Key Interview/Real-Time Statement
In modern cloud environments, we do not manually add new server IPs to inventory files.

ASG launches new EC2 instances.
AWS tags the instances.
Ansible Dynamic Inventory (aws_ec2 plugin) queries AWS APIs and automatically discovers the new servers based on tags.
AWX/Jenkins then executes playbooks against those discovered hosts via SSH or AWS SSM.

So we manage Tags and Host Groups, not individual IP addresses.
Actual Enterprise Thinking
Old World:
Server ---> IP ---> Add to inventory manually

Modern World:
Server ---> Tags ---> Dynamic Inventory ---> Automatic Discovery

This "Tags → Dynamic Inventory → Automatic Discovery → Playbook Execution" pattern is what you will commonly see in AWS-based enterprise environments.
